  "rationale": "Single hero on the hero-event-meta-forward archetype: the tracked caption meta row leads (the facts ARE the pitch and carry the news/urgency register, so no NEW badge or countdown), the event name 'Spotlight' takes the licensed hero-scale display moment typeset in the brand's own display face (ink on the warm cream raised band \u2014 accent text is not licensed on a light surface, so orange stays in the primary button and the six Hub product marks), one promise line advances the meta without inflating (AS-51), and a single primary 'Save my seat' beside a quiet ghost sibling honors AS-59. The agenda rail renders the six real Hub product-icon assets as the quiet agenda-at-a-glance with one caption line \u2014 never louder than the name. Surface is 'raised' per the copy-first plan; no media slot, matching the brief's deliberate omission of atmosphere photography, speaker strip and venue. Off-grid unlocked but not needed \u2014 disciplined clean-SaaS alignment serves this copy best."
